A fairness-based logistic decision model that computes the normalized deviation between the proposed share (split_self) and the fairness norm (token_self×£3) relative to the total available money (combined_earning). The model uses two learnable parameters (beta and tau) to generate a predicted probability of acceptance, which is then scaled by split_self to yield the expected accepted amount for responder trials.
</SUMMARY>

